@node description "Description"
------------
DESCRIPTION:
------------

Welcome to Insulter. I wrote this program as lately more and more people on
the newsgroups and in email are being far from civil. And I so hate wasting
time on counter insults. I'd much rather have Amy do that for me. *grin* So
this resulted in 'Insulter' A tiny program that creates random insults that
are even fun to read.  It handles both contemporary form as well as classic
form. Like old Shakespearian types of insults.  Insulter has an easy to use 
standard AmigaGUI and requires no 3rd party libraries. All that's needed is
for you to select the 'insult mode' and click on the 'Insult!' button. Then
a random insult is generated in the string gadget at the bottom part of the
window. I picked a string gadget as it is very easy to select it's contents
and copy and paste those into another application. All that is needed is to
click 'Right Amiga - B" to start a block, use the mouse to select the whole
insult and then 'Right Amiga C' to copy it and finally 'Right Amiga - V' to
paste it somewhere.  Of course the program has an extensive ARexx host that
allows you to select the mode and retrieve insults via ARexx. So it is very
easy to integrate Insulter with a mailer, newsreader, web-browser or editor
that has decent ARexx support. This program is also font sensitive.  


        +-----------------------------------------------------+
        |o| Insulter v1.1, ©1998 by  Paul Kolenbrander    | | |
        +-----------------------------------------------------+
        |              ______   _______  _________  ________  |
        | Insult Mode |______| |_About_||_Insult!_||_Speak!_| |
        |  _________________________________________________  |
        | |_________________________________________________| |
        |                                                     |
        +-----------------------------------------------------+

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: Only for those who have the old AmigaDOS 'speech' support installed!!
      If AmigaDOS 'speech' support is not, or not correctly/fully installed
      the 'Speak!' gadget will be ghosted. Otherwise it will be active.  

If speech support is installed on your Amiga, you may then use the 'Speak!'
button instead of the 'Insult!' one to generate an insult. And not only see
it displayed but hear it spoken as well. As this technology seems no longer
supported. I've done it the quick way by calling the 'Say' program from the
Insulter program. A consequence of this is that the 'Say' program has to be
where it is put default on installation, the 'Sys:utilities' drawer. If you
don't have it there, the insult won't be spoken. You can then use the Arexx
script further below to archieve spoken insults. But modify the path to the
say program there so it reflects your setup.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

New options for Version 1.1

- Allows setting of voice, speed and pitch for Say command
- Allows setting of path for Say command. If no path supplied Insulter will
  default to SYS:Utilities.
- Allows for outputting an insult to the CLI. Now making it possible to run
  Insulter from eg. S:User-Startup, S:Shell-Startup or a cron type tool.
- Allows for speaking an insult without opening it's window. Similar to the
  CLI output above. Have your Amiga boot with an insult to her user. 
- ARexx support for voice, speed and pitch setting for the Say command.

@endnode

@node parameters "Tooltypes and CLI parameters"

It allows for a number of CLI parameters and Tooltypes. Which are:

'PUBSCREEN=' Enables you to specify a public screen CountryCodes is to open
             its window on. Default value for this parameter is, of course,
             the Workbench screen. Usage: PUBSCREEN=Edit_screen.

'SAYPATH='   Specify the path to the Say command. Better not input a faulty
             path as Insulter won't let you get away with that.

'SAYVOICE='  Specify the voice to use. Select from female, male, robot or
             neutral.

'SAYPITCH='  Specify the pitch to use. Insert a value between 65 and 300.

'SAYSPEED='  Specify the speed to use. Insert a value between 40 and 400.

'CLIONLY'    When specified, Insulter will not open it's window but output
             an insult to the CLI/Shell window it was started from.

'SPEAKONLY'  When specified, Insulter will not open it's window but output
             an insult via the Say command. This does requires functional
             speech and a correct path to the Say command.

'FONTNAME='  Specify (fixed width) font to use. Usage: FONTNAME=Topaz.font

'FONTSIZE='  Specify the size of the font to use. Usage: FONTSIZE=11

'TOPEDGE='   Y position for the window to open on. Usage: TOPEDGE=10

'LEFTEDGE='  X position for the window to open on. Usage: LEFTEDGE=50

'ZOOMTOP='   X position of iconified window. Usage: ZOOMTOP=30

'ZOOMLEFT='  Y position of iconified window. Usage: ZOOMLEFT=20 

* Note: CLIONLY and SPEAKONLY parameters may be used together. But when one
        or both are used, Insulter's ARexx host is NOT active.

@endnode

@node arexx "ARexx Interface"
---------------
AREXX COMMANDS:
---------------

No selfrespecting Amiga program would complete without a decent ARexx Host.
Insulter is no exception to this rule.  It has an extensive ARexx host that
allows you to activate, send back, bring front and even move its window. It
also supports insult mode being set via ARexx instead of inputted directly.
As well as retrieving the insult.  Allowing for the construction of scripts
that should easily interface with any mailer/newsreader or WWW browser with
ARexx support. The ARexx hostname for this program is INSULT1. You can also
find the ARexx hostname in the 'About' Requester.  Any subsequent hosts are
named: INSULTx (where x is a number).


CLASSIC                    - Set Classic Insult mode.

NORMAL                     - Set Contemporary Insult mode.

INSULT!                    - Retrieve an insult from the program.

SPEAK!                     - Generates and Speaks a random insult!

SEEDME                     - Reseed the random routine. The seeder uses the
                             current system time as it's seed.

SAY MALE                   - Set voice to Male.

SAY FEMALE                 - Set voice to Female.

SAY ROBOT                  - Set voice to Robot.

SAY NEUTRAL                - Set voice to Neutral.

SAY PITCH val              - Set Say pitch. (val should be between 65 - 300)
                             Eg. SAY PITCH 200

SAY SPEED val              - Set Say speed. (val should be between 40 - 400)
                             Eg. SAY SPEED 150

WINDOW ACTIVATE            - Activate the window.

WINDOW MOVE xval yval      - Move the window. Always specify both the x & y
                             values. Eg. WINDOW MOVE 0 10.

WINDOW BACK                - Push the window back.   

WINDOW FRONT               - Bring the window back to the front.

WINDOW POSITION            - Returns the window x and y position as well as
                             it's width and height. Eg. '10 200 566 89'

QUIT                       - End the program.


To move Insulter window to front (assuming ARexx host is INSULT1) : 
rx 'ADDRESS INSULT1 WINDOW FRONT'

To move Insulter window 50 pixels to the right and 10 down:
rx 'ADDRESS INSULT1 WINDOW MOVE 50 10'

To set 'classic' insult mode::
rx 'ADDRESS INSULT1 CLASSIC'

And to end Insulter:
rx 'ADDRESS INSULT1 QUIT'

And a small script to get an insult from the program:
------------------------- Script Begin ------------------------- 
/* Get an Insult */

options results

ADDRESS INSULT1

INSULT!
say 'Here is the insult chief!'
say result
exit
-------------------------- Script End -------------------------- 

For a final blow, why not feed the insult to the 'Say' program? This will
only work if you have the AmigaDOS 'speech' installed and functioning. As
that part is not included with AmigaDOS 3.0. Which is a pity. Anyhow, here
is an Arexx script that speaks the insults.

------------------------- Script Begin ------------------------- 
/* Get and speak an Insult */

options results

ADDRESS INSULT1

INSULT!
say 'Here is the insult chief!'
ADDRESS COMMAND 'say ' ||result
exit
-------------------------- Script End -------------------------- 

This program does send standard return codes that can be evaluated by your 
arexx script to determine if the command was succesful.

@endnode

