2. Add support for user definable insult collections. I'm mulling over the
   exact layout and procedure to do that. But somthing in this vein should
   find it's way into a future version.


---------
TO DON'T:
---------

This is the stuff you need not bother asking me because it won't happen.

1. A MUI version. No way Jose. First of all I don't like MUI. To the point
   I dislike it's implementation and the constraint it has on programmers.
   And secondly, this GUI is so simple it does not need MUI. And just like
   you are free to use MUI, I am free not to use it. Or program for it.

2. A ClassAct version. Perhaps.. The problem is that Insulter is giftware,
   and to use ClassAct as a developer you need to buy a license. If a nice
   person out there gifts me such a license, I might just move this to the
   To DO section instead of here.

3. Built-in timer support for random time generated insults. Come on guys!
   It has ARexx. I don't favor the school of 'everyting including the dang
   kitchen sink' of programming. Especially when it is not needed. See the
   @{"ARexx examples" link rexxamples} section of this document for a very
   versatile script that does just this.

@endnode

