@node problems "Problems and Solutions"
--------------------
PROBLEMS & SOLUTIONS
--------------------

Q. The 'Speak!' gadget is ghosted and I have speech installed.
A. The program checks on the existence of 4 files. If one or more of
   these are missing it means speech may not be installed correctly
   and the program does not enable support. These files are:
   a. libs:translator.library
   b. devs:narrator.device
   c. L:speak-handler
   d. say (in the user inputted or teh system path)
   Make sure these files are present and at the above locations. 

Q. I press the 'Speak!' gadget and although the insult is displayed
   it is not spoken.
A. There are a few possible problems for this.
   a. Do you have speakers connected to your Amiga?
   b. Are the speakers switched on and is the volume level high 
      enough? Can you hear the system 'errorbeep'? If no, check
      speakere connections and volume levels.
   c. You may have a faulty or incomplete installation of the Amiga
      speech. Please run the "sys:utilities/say' program and input
      some text. Unless it speaks your text something is wrong with
      Amiga speech. Please correct it. If you have Say in another
      directory, use the @{"SAYPATH" link parameters} parameter when starting Insulter.

Q. I can't seem to copy the insult.
A. a. Click the mouse in the stringgadget containing the insult and
      make sure the 'text cursor' that now appears is on the far left
      of the gadget.
   b. Simultaniously press the 'Right Amiga' and 'B' keys to activate
      block mode.
   c. Use the mouse, or the 'cursor right' (right arrow) key to mark
      the whole insult.
   d. Now simultaniously press 'Right Amiga' and 'C' keys to copy the
      insult you just marked to the clipboard.
   e. Now you can paste it into any Amiga application that supports
      the Amiga standard clipboard by simultaniously pressing the
      'Right Amiga' and 'V' keys. 

Q. I set a font using the FONTNAME= tooltype or CLI parameter and 
   the program doesn't use it.
A. Make sure of the following:
   a. The font you specified is a fixed width font. Only those are
      supported by the program.
   b. You specified the font name correctly, eg. 'topaz.font' and
      not 'topaz' or 'fonts:topaz.font'.

Q. I set a font size using the FONTSIZE= tooltype or CLI parameter
   and the program doesn't use it.
A. Make sure of the following:
   a. You have to use the FONTSIZE parameter in conjunction with a 
      FONTNAME parameter. 
   b. Make sure that the size you specified does really exist for
      the font you specified.
   c. The program checks if it can open a window that is still 
      within the screen constraints using the font size that you
      specified. If it cannot, it defaults to using the system
      default font. So eg. FONTSIZE=75 probably will fail because 
      of this very reason.

@endnode

@node history "History"
-------
HISTORY
-------

20-jun-1998   Added 'SPEAK!" and 'SEEDME' ARexx support after getting
(v1.1)        requests for those. Also came up with some nice example
              Arexx scripts. Which are included in this document

14-jun-1998   After feedback in mail and in c.s.a.programmer, support
              for Say has been extensively enhanced to a point where 
              one can set the path for it, set the type of voice, the
              speed and the pitch upon startup. The latter 3 can also
              be modified via the ARexx host with simple commands. I
              also implemented CLI Only and Speak Only modes for the
              people who like to run it from a cron type tool or in
              their User-Startup.

06-jun-1998 - Insulter v1.0 released. Basically a gag I came up with 
(v1.0)        after Mr. Tim Rue in c.s.a.misc went as far as comparing
              programmers to Hitler. This caused him to be kicked into
              my kill/jerk file and sparked Insulter. Support for Say
              got put in as an afterthought though but turned out to
              be quite popular.

@endnode

@node rexxamples "ARexx Example Scripts"

Here are a few example ARexx script to show the power of ARexx. And to
help you on your ay into making better use of Insulter. If you've made
any handy ARexx script for Insulter you would like included below just
mail it to me at paul@iaehv.nl.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
/*
 * Speak Insults at random times.
 * Author      : Paul Kolenbrander.
 * Date Written: 20th june 1998
 * Requirements: Say and Wait should be in your path. Insulter running
*/

OPTIONS RESULTS
mintime = 1               /* Set minimum time between insults */
maxtime = 15              /* Set maximum time between insults */
                          /* delay time is in minutes         */

ADDRESS INSULT1           /* change this if needed            */

WINDOW BACK

delay = RANDOM(mintime,maxtime, TIME('M') * TIME('S') )

DO FOREVER                /* keep it up until eternity        */
   delay = RANDOM(mintime,maxtime)
   ADDRESS COMMAND 'Wait ' || delay || ' min'
   WINDOW FRONT
   SPEAK!
   ADDRESS COMMAND 'Wait 3 sec'
   WINDOW BACK
END

EXIT
----------------------------------------------------------------------
/*
 * Generate an insult and feed it to the SPEAK: Device
 * Author      : Paul Kolenbrander.
 * Date Written: 21th june 1998
 * Requirements: Insulter should be running and SPEAK: mounted.
*/
OPTIONS RESULTS

ADDRESS INSULT1

INSULT!
ADDRESS COMMAND 'C:ECHO ' || result || " to SPEAK:OPT/f/"

EXIT
----------------------------------------------------------------------
/*
 * Generate an insult and insert it into CygnusEd 3.5. (eg in a mail)
 * Author      : Paul Kolenbrander.
 * Date Written: 20th june 1998
 * Requirements: Insulter and CygnusEd should be running. Just install
 *               this one in CygnusEd (See CygnusEd Manual) so you can
 *               run it from eg. a function key.
*/

OPTIONS RESULTS

ADDRESS INSULT1
INSULT!
insult = result

ADDRESS 'rexx_ced'
TEXT insult
EXIT
----------------------------------------------------------------------
/*
 * Generate an insult and insert it into GoldEd 3/4. (eg in a mail)
 * Author      : Paul Kolenbrander.
 * Date Written: 20th june 1998
 * Requirements: Insulter and GoldEd should be running.
*/

OPTIONS RESULTS

ADDRESS INSULT1
INSULT!
insult = result

ADDRESS 'GOLDED.1'
'LOCK CURRENT RELEASE=4'                 /* lock GUI, gain access   */
                                         /* remove the 'RELEASE=4'  */
                                         /* part if GoldEd 3.x...   */
OPTIONS FAILAT 6                         /* ignore warnings         */
SIGNAL ON SYNTAX                         /* ensure clean exit       */

'FOLD ALL OPEN=TRUE'                     /* open all folds          */
'TEXT T=' insult
'UNLOCK'                                 /* And unlock the GUI      */
EXIT
----------------------------------------------------------------------

@endnode
